article.headline: Cal Poly 23, Humboldt St. 17
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. -- Quarterback Tony Smith threw for a touchdown and ran for another to lead Cal Poly-San Luis Obispo past Humboldt State 23-17 on Saturday night. Smith connected on 6 of 12 passes for 39 yards, but it was his 48-yard scoring dash late in the third quarter that put the Mustangs (1-0) on top for good. Slotback Mark Rodgers ran for 106 yards and a touchdown and pulled down Smith's scoring pass in the second quarter. The Luberjacks (0-1) were up 17-7 at halftime thanks to an 8-yard pass from Mike Proulx to Dirk Dallas late in the first quarter, a 40-yard field goal by Matt Bruder in the second and a 29-yard fumble recovery and run by Jonathan Faraimo just before the break. After coming back in the second half, the Mustangs topped of their victory with a safety by James Chen with about eight minutes left.
